%N A396463 Consider the square spiral in the first quadrant with its cells numbered starting at 0. Three players take turns and place black knights(K), cyan antelopes(A), and red ferzes(F), respectively, at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing pieces of a different color. Sequence lists squares occupied by a red ferz.
%C A396463 A variant of A392177 with three players with different fairy chess pieces.
%H A396463 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396463/b396463.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396463 Brady Haran, Jonas Karlsson, and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://youtu.be/UiX4CFIiegM">Red & Black Knights (extraordinary result)</a>;<a href="https://youtu.be/VgmDuBCayPw">Amazing Chessboard Patterns (extra)</a>, YouTube Numberphile videos, May 2026
